cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.PF, cs.MA 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with the queuing behaviour of real Internet traffic. It could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) as it discusses the notion of long-range dependence in traffic modelling. Additionally, it could be classified under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with the behaviour of real traffic traces. It may also be relevant to cs.PF (Performance) as it investigates the queuing performance of traffic. Finally, it could be classified under cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) as it deals with modelling and simulating traffic.
